summary: the captain marvel scene where she blasts yon rogg mid-speech is essentially just hulk smashing loki mid speech and people are...
question: the captain marvel scene where she blasts yon rogg mid-speech is essentially just hulk smashing loki mid speech and people are too caught up in the arguments of feminism to realize marvel is literally just following their formula of "Bad guy makes big speech. hero cuts them off mid way and kicks their ass"   it's only controversial with marvel because she's a woman.
answer:
i see what you’re saying, and i agree to an extent, but i do think there’s more to it in the case of captain marvel.

in this case, the scene says something about carol and her development, rather than simply following the same marvel formula. yon-rogg eggs her on, doing the same manipulative thing he’s been doing with carol for six years – and while carol at the beginning of the movie might have been baited into it, because she’s been told constantly that she needs to prove herself (even well before the crash and the loss of her memories), her journey over the course of this movie is learning that she doesn’t. this isn’t quip-quip-punch or any other kind of stock marvel moment, it’s a character statement.

there are a lot of things that captain marvel does as a movie to follow the marvel formula, where it’s really suspicious that people have a problem with them in this case and not in the case of white male protagonist #6, but this particular moment actually stands out in my mind as being something uniquely carol.
